OL,3,C'I feel like a second-class citizen':
OL,4,CPlea for help from disabled people
OL,6,FThat is because, unlike the UK, Jersey
OL,7,Fand Guernsey do not have specific
OL,8,Fsubsidies for those who may rely on
OL,9,Felectricity to stay alive, such as
OL,10,Fpowering oxygen concentrators, for
OL,11,Fextra heating or charging a wheelchair.
OL,13,FJersey resident Dan Dicker has
OL,14,Fcerebral palsy and uses a wheelchair;
OL,15,Fas bills continue to climb, he wonders
OL,16,Fwhether the island is still a suitable
OL,17,Fplace to live with a disability.
OL,19,F"I am struggling," he says.
